{"TopicId":98364,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Find Part of GameObject","CreatedByName":"lo-fi","CreatedById":111099,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-31T14:08:43Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"lo-fi","CreatedById":111099,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-31T14:08:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHi guys\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAs the title says, I\u0027m sure I remember seeing a method something like GOToPart(GameObject) that returned the instance of the part the passed GO is attached to.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI can\u0027t seem to dig it out of the object browser and searches haven\u0027t turned up anything helpful, so I wonder if someone could point me in the right direction? \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMany thanks!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"philotical","CreatedById":109390,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-31T17:48:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Esomething like\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPart p = go.GetComponentInParent\u0026lt;Part\u0026gt;() as Part;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eshould do the trick..\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-01-31T17:50:34Z\u0022 title=\u002201/31/2015 05:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 31, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by philotical\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lo-fi","CreatedById":111099,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-31T19:20:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAh, thank you. That will recursively search up the hierarchy?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"philotical","CreatedById":109390,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-31T19:41:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Eyw\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Erecursively: yup\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Component.GetComponentInParent.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Component.GetComponentInParent.html\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}